issue.title: Fix Cli
issue.body:
Java-cli wasn't working properly so I made some changes. 
1. cli now can query multiple school and subject for query.catalog
2. cli now take either term (the shortcut version) OR year and semester to construct a term. Semester will be "fa", "sp", etc..

issue.title: Credits
issue.body: We currently have all the course data but they are all currently missing how many credits each class has. We should find a solution to this in the future.

issue.title: Code comments
issue.body: There are lots of added new features that are missing comments for the code. This will be good first issue to understand Schedge codebase by reading through the code and adding comments.

issue.title: Refactor Kotlin Code to Java
issue.body:
## Refactor Kotlin Code into Java
- Turn objects and enums in nyu_models.kt into objects and enums in Java
- Using Apache Async HttpComponents and Apache HttpClient to handle AsyncRequest to Albert Mobile in Java
### Finished:
- Objects and Enums to hold data, similar to nyu_models.kt
- query catalog, query section, query subject based on the term without batch process. 

### To Do:
- [x]  Add batch process in each query
- [ ]  Test batch process 
- [x] Add Scraping 
- [x] Add CLI for Java Code with picoli 
- [x] Add utils class to handle I/O to File

### Note:
- I will keep pushing more code to this branch if this looks fine. If not, let me know.
